# Theme repo map

## Source of truth vs output

| Role | Path |
| ---- | ---- |
| Edit CSS here | `themes/addons/vscode-preview/original/<family>/vscode-preview-*.css` |
| Build script | `themes/addons/vscode-preview/build-mpe-global.mjs` |
| Generated packages | `themes/mpe/released/<slug>/style.less` or `themes/mpe/experimental/<slug>/style.less` |
| Released Crossnote config | `themes/mpe/released/<slug>/config.js` (required for released; full katex/mathjax/mermaidConfig) |

Do **not** hand-edit generated `style.less` unless the user explicitly asks. Change source CSS, then rebuild.

```bash
node themes/addons/vscode-preview/build-mpe-global.mjs
```

New variants default to `tier: "experimental"`. Only promote to `released` with a package-local `config.js`.

## Addons (not tier-split)

- `themes/addons/vscode-preview/` — shared authoring + optional `markdown.styles`
- `themes/addons/cursor-inline/` — legacy; prefer MPE released; do not create for new themes unless asked

## Shared CSS appended by build

Always: `_scope.css`, `_syntax-tokens.css`  
Optional: `_diagram-tokens.css` (`appendDiagramTokens: true`), graphite refine (`appendSyntaxRefine: true`)

## Mermaid

- Config: `themes/mpe/released/cpp-modern/config.js` (dark) or `themes/mpe/released/cpp-modern-light/config.js` (light) → paste over `%USERPROFILE%\.crossnote\config.js` (same `({ … })` shape)
- Deep dive: `docs/mermaid-styling.md`
- Prefer config over fighting SVG with preview CSS alone

## Fixtures and iteration

- Markdown: `examples/mermaid-showcase.md`, `examples/code-showcase.md`
- Browser workbench: `preview/` — iterate UI, then hand off CSS into `original/`
- Install docs: `themes/mpe/README.md`, `themes/README.md`
- Theme anatomy (tokens / selectors / config): `docs/mpe-theme-reference.md`

## Commit after major changes

When finishing a **major** theme/Mermaid/docs unit of work in this repo, **create a git commit** (do not wait for the user to ask). This overrides the usual “only commit when asked” default for this project.

**Major** (commit once the unit is done):

- New family or named variant (CSS + registry + rebuild + README touchpoints)
- Promote experimental → released (Mermaid JSON + tier flip + docs)
- Substantial Mermaid / Crossnote `config.js` change (not a one-line typo)
- Package layout / build pipeline / install-path docs overhaul
- New or rewritten Cursor skill / rule that changes agent workflow

**Not major** (batch or skip): tiny typo fixes, drive-by comment edits, mid-iteration WIP while still iterating colors.

**How:** follow the repo git commit protocol (`git status` / `diff` / `log` style, stage relevant files only, HEREDOC message focused on why, no `--no-verify`, no amend unless rules allow, **do not push** unless the user asks). One logical change → one commit; if several majors land in one session, prefer separate commits per unit.
